    "title": "Opening for Medical Officer at Bombay Hospital South Asia Partners",
    "description": "Are you a skilled Medical Officer looking for your next big career move? Bombay Hospital South Asia Partners in Allahabad offers you the perfect platform to grow professionally and personally.\n\nAbout Bombay Hospital South Asia Partners:\nBombay Hospital South Asia Partners is a leading organization in the Hybrid sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Provide high-quality patient care and maintain patient records\n• Educate patients and families on health management and disease prevention\n• Diagnose and treat medical conditions following established protocols\n• Attend continuing medical education programs and training\n• Maintain sterile environments and follow infection control protocols\n• Adhere to NABH/JCI accreditation standards\n• Monitor patient progress and adjust treatment plans accordingly\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• Chartered Accountant (ICAI)\n• 10-15 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in Pharmacovigilance\n• Proficiency in CPT Codes\n• Proficiency in Clinical Research\n• Proficiency in Medical Coding\n• Proficiency in Telemedicine\n• Proficiency in Medical Ethics\n• Proficiency in Medical Terminology\n• Proficiency in HIPAA Compliance\n\nWork Mode: Hybrid - Flexible work-from-home and office\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Competitive salary with performance-linked incentives\n• Learning & development budget\n• Comprehensive health insurance for self and family\n• Life and accident insurance\n• Provident Fund and Gratuity as per company policy\n• Annual paid leaves and casual leaves\n• Salary Range: 20 LPA - 40 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Allahabad, Uttar Pradesh, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with Bombay Hospital South Asia Partners!",
